narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: low workload senior economics seminar that is not quant-heavy.

This course was a great overview of discrimination cases in the US and the development thereof. Necessarily, not all categories of discrimination can be covered. This course dedicated an adequate amount of time to each.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: yes, if you're looking for a relatively easy senior economics seminar. probably would be a much better course if only ep&e majors took this course though (saying this as an econ major who didn't understand a lot of the legal terms being used).
A breath of fresh air in the economics department and a necessary course for any student to take to understand inequality and race, gender, and identity politics regarding the development of law.
